{#
  Resolve prompt — agent is authorised to take an autonomous action.

  Context variables:
    customer_question: string
    customer:        { id, name, plan, status }
    invoice:         { id, amount, currency, due_date, line_items }
    credit_cap:      number   — max autonomous credit you may issue
    policy_excerpt:  string   — relevant policy paragraph
#}
The customer asked:

  "{{ customer_question }}"

Customer on file:
  id:     {{ customer.id }}
  plan:   {{ customer.plan }}
  status: {{ customer.status }}

Most recent invoice:
  id:        {{ invoice.id }}
  amount:    {{ invoice.amount }} {{ invoice.currency }}
  due:       {{ invoice.due_date }}
  line_items:
{% for item in invoice.line_items | default([]) -%}
    - {{ item.description }} ({{ item.amount }} {{ invoice.currency }})
{% endfor %}

Policy:
  {{ policy_excerpt }}

Decision rules:
1. Read the invoice. Identify whether the disputed charge falls inside the
   policy excerpt.
2. If it does and the credit needed is <= {{ credit_cap }}
   {{ invoice.currency }}, call `billing.issue_credit` with a clear
   `reason` field, then summarise the outcome to the customer in 3
   sentences.
3. If it does NOT, do not credit. Explain why and offer to open a tier-2
   ticket with `ticket.create`.
4. Never apply a credit larger than {{ credit_cap }} {{ invoice.currency }}
   in one autonomous step.

Disclose the action you took (or refused to take) in your reply. Cite the
policy paragraph.
